  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Installation Engineer",
  "description": "<ul><li>Travel to various sites to supervise the on-site installation of outdoor camera systems (CCTV, security cameras, etc.)</li><li>Lead and coordinate a team of technicians, installers, and subcontractors.</li><li>Conduct site assessments to determine the most effective camera placements and configurations.</li><li>Collaborate with clients to understand their specific needs and ensure their satisfaction throughout the project.</li><li>Troubleshooting, maintenance, and resolving any technical issues related to the installation of the systems.</li><li>Monitor the progress of installations to ensure they are completed on time and within budget.</li><li>Perform quality control checks to ensure systems are functioning correctly before handover to the client.</li><li>Maintain accurate records of installation activities, materials used, and any issues encountered on site.</li><li>Train and mentor junior technicians and installers to ensure high standards of performance and safety.</li><li>Provide regular reports to management regarding project progress, challenges, and completion timelines.</li><li>Ensure that all equipment and tools are maintained and used properly to avoid damage or loss.</li><li>Ensure all work is completed efficiently and according to project specifications.</li><li>Ensure that all safety protocols and industry regulations are followed during the installation process.</li><li>Carry equipment and work in various outdoor weather conditions.</li><li>Climb ladders and work at heights for camera installations.</li></ul>",
